    caption: [The (cid:3) oxidation of fatty acids in the endoplasmic reticu- lum. This alternative to (cid:2) oxidation begins with oxidation of the carbon most distant from the (cid:2) carbon—the (cid:3) (omega) carbon. The substrate is usually a medium-chain fatty acid; shown here is lauric acid (laurate). This pathway is generally not the major route for oxidative catabolism of fatty acids.],
